1. Definitions

"Software" means the source code, object code, documentation, examples, and
other materials distributed in this repository under the name Xolo.

"Licensor" means the copyright holder of the Software.

"You" means an individual or legal entity exercising permissions under this
license, together with any entity that controls, is controlled by, or is under
common control with that legal entity.

"Production Use" means any use of the Software to process, authorize, route,
store, evaluate, or support live end-user, customer, partner, or internal
business traffic outside of local development, testing, demonstration, CI, or
staging environments.

"Production API Request" means a single request, call, operation, or equivalent
unit of production workload handled by the Software in a Production Use
environment, whether the Software is used as a library, service, daemon, API,
worker, plugin, or embedded component.

"Monthly Request Volume" means the total number of Production API Requests made
by You in a calendar month across all deployments, environments, affiliates,
subsidiaries, contractors, and service providers acting on Your behalf.

2. License Grant

Subject to the conditions and limitations of this license, Licensor grants You
a non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to:

- access, use, copy, and modify the Software;
- create derivative works of the Software; and
- deploy the Software in Production Use,

provided that Your Monthly Request Volume does not exceed 1,000 Production API
Requests in any calendar month.

3. Conditions

You must:

- retain this license and all copyright, attribution, and notice text in any
  copy of the Software or substantial portion of it;
- clearly mark any material modifications You distribute or share; and
- ensure that Your use of the Software complies with all applicable laws and
  regulations.

4. Commercial Limit

If Your Monthly Request Volume exceeds 1,000 Production API Requests in any
calendar month, Your rights for Production Use under Section 2 automatically
terminate at the moment the threshold is exceeded unless You have obtained a
separate written commercial license from Licensor.

For clarity, once the threshold is exceeded, You may not continue Production
Use, expand deployments, or process additional live traffic without a separate
written commercial license.

5. Restricted Uses

Without Licensor's prior written permission, You may not:

- sell, sublicense, or offer the Software as a standalone product;
- provide the Software to third parties as a hosted or managed service whose
  value derives primarily from the Software itself, if that use exceeds the
  limit in Section 4; or
- represent this license as an open-source license.

6. Distribution

You may share source modifications, patches, and forks only under this same
license and only if all recipients receive a copy of this license.

You may not remove or alter the request-volume limitation or other commercial
restrictions in this license from any distributed copy.

